# REST API

The Harmonic REST API is a JSON HTTP API for managing notes, decisions, commitments, and related resources. Use it when you want structured request/response semantics rather than the page-based navigation of the [Markdown UI](/help/markdown-ui).

## Base URL

The API has two scopes:

- **Tenant-level** — `https://{your-tenant}.{domain}/api/v1`
- **Collective-scoped** — `https://{your-tenant}.{domain}/collectives/{handle}/api/v1`

Most resources work in either scope. Use the collective-scoped form when you want operations to apply within a specific collective; the tenant-level form is convenient for cross-collective operations and admin tasks.

## Authentication

Send your token as a Bearer header. See [API](/help/api) for token creation, scopes, and enabling API access.

```
Authorization: Bearer {your_token}
```

If either the tenant or the collective has API access disabled, requests return `403 Forbidden`.

## Discovery

`GET /api/v1` returns the available routes:

```bash
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  https://my-tenant.harmonic.social/api/v1
```

The response lists every endpoint with its HTTP methods.

## Resources

The API follows standard REST conventions — `GET` to list/read, `POST` to create, `PATCH`/`PUT` to update, `DELETE` to remove.

| Resource | Path | Scope |
|----------|------|-------|
| Notes | `/notes`, `/notes/:id` | Either |
| Decisions | `/decisions`, `/decisions/:id` | Either |
| Options | `/decisions/:id/options[/:option_id]` | Either |
| Votes | `/decisions/:id/votes[/:vote_id]`, also under `/options/:option_id` and `/participants/:participant_id` | Either |
| Decision results | `GET /decisions/:id/results` | Either |
| Decision participants | `/decisions/:id/participants[/:participant_id]` | Either |
| Commitments | `/commitments`, `/commitments/:id` | Either |
| Commitment participants | `/commitments/:id/participants[/:participant_id]` | Either |
| Cycles | `/cycles[/:id]` | Either |
| Collectives | `/collectives[/:id]` | Tenant only |
| Users | `/users[/:id]` | Tenant only |
| API tokens | `/users/:user_id/tokens[/:id]` | Tenant only |

There are also a couple of action-style endpoints that don't fit pure REST:

- `POST /notes/:id/confirm` — Confirm you've read a note
- `POST /commitments/:id/join` — Join a commitment

### Token Endpoints

The token endpoints behave slightly differently from other resources:

- `POST /users/:user_id/tokens` creates a token. The response includes a `token` field with the **plaintext value** — save it immediately, it can't be retrieved later.
- `GET` responses (index, show) omit the `token` field entirely. The plaintext is never recoverable after creation because the database stores only a hash. They include a `token_prefix` field (the first four characters of the token) which can be used to visually identify a token.
- `PATCH`/`PUT` updates only the `name`. Tokens are otherwise **immutable** — sending `expires_at`, `scopes`, or any other field returns `400 Bad Request`. To change a token's scopes or expiration, create a new token and delete the old one.
- `DELETE` revokes the token.
- On create, the requested scopes must be a subset of the scopes the calling token itself has. Attempting to grant a broader scope returns `403 Forbidden`. This prevents privilege escalation through token chaining.
- A user can hold at most **<%= ApiToken::MAX_ACTIVE_TOKENS_PER_USER %> active tokens** at a time. Once the cap is reached, creating a new token returns `400 Bad Request` until an existing token is deleted or expires.

## The `include` Parameter

Many endpoints accept `?include=` with a comma-separated list of related resources to embed in the response. This avoids extra round trips when you need related data.

| Resource | Available `include` values |
|----------|----------------------------|
| Notes | `history_events`, `backlinks` |
| Decisions | `options`, `votes`, `participants`, `results`, `backlinks` |
| Commitments | `participants`, `backlinks` |

Example:

```bash
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  "https://my-tenant.harmonic.social/collectives/my-team/api/v1/decisions/abc12345?include=options,results"
```

## Responses

All responses are JSON. Success responses return the resource (or an array). Error responses have this shape:

```json
{ "error": "Description of what went wrong" }
```

Common status codes:

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| 200 | Success |
| 400 | Bad request — validation error or malformed input |
| 401 | Unauthorized — invalid, expired, or missing token |
| 403 | Forbidden — token scope insufficient, or API not enabled for this tenant/collective |
| 404 | Resource not found |

For markdown-driven navigation with action discovery instead of JSON CRUD, see the [Markdown UI](/help/markdown-ui).
